      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A durable power of attorney is a legal instrument that designates an agent to act on your father's behalf, with the specific condition that this authority **survives** the death of your father.\n\nHere is the breakdown of the legal mechanics:\n\n1.  **Termination upon Death:** The authority of a standard (non-durable) power of attorney terminates immediately upon the death of the principal (your father). Once he passes, the document is void, and the agent loses all legal standing to make decisions.\n2.  **Continuation in Durable Form:** In a durable power of attorney, the clause stating that the authority survives incapacity and death is the defining feature. The agent retains the legal right to make financial and medical decisions **until** the agent themselves dies, or until a successor agent is formally appointed by the court.\n\nEssentially, the durable version acts as a bridge that keeps the power of attorney active even after the original owner is gone, preventing the estate from becoming a legal vacuum.",
